There! Ow!

172
00:13:24,002 --> 00:13:26,002
Throw it!

173
00:13:26,002 --> 00:13:28,002
You can't hit it!

174
00:13:28,002 --> 00:13:30,002
Yes! Ow!

175
00:13:30,002 --> 00:13:32,002
That's what you thought!

176
00:13:32,002 --> 00:13:34,002
That's what you thought!

177
00:13:34,002 --> 00:13:36,002
Hit it!

178
00:13:36,002 --> 00:13:38,002
Hit it!

179
00:13:38,002 --> 00:13:40,002
Yes!

180
00:13:40,002 --> 00:13:42,002
Now mine!

181
00:13:42,002 --> 00:13:44,002
Wait, I'm coming!

182
00:13:44,002 --> 00:13:46,002
You have to be faster!

183
00:13:46,002 --> 00:13:48,002
That wasn't anything!

184
00:13:48,002 --> 00:13:50,002
And again!

185
00:13:50,002 --> 00:13:52,002
I'm with you!

186
00:13:52,002 --> 00:13:54,002
Ow!

187
00:13:54,002 --> 00:13:56,002
A bomb!

188
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:58,002
Yes!

189
00:13:58,002 --> 00:14:00,002
A bomb!

190
00:14:04,002 --> 00:14:06,002
One!

191
00:14:10,070 --> 00:14:12,070
What does she want?

192
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:16,070
Heidi, come with me. It's late!

193
00:14:17,070 --> 00:14:19,070
Why don't you go on?

194
00:14:20,070 --> 00:14:23,070
Are you frozen or what?

195
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:27,070
Are you Heidi from the Alp?

196
00:14:28,070 --> 00:14:30,070
Yes, of course I am.

197
00:14:33,070 --> 00:14:36,070
Why don't you go to school when you're already down here?

198
00:14:36,070 --> 00:14:37,070
Why me?

199
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:40,684
The teacher gave you a letter. Tell me, did you lose it somewhere?

200
00:14:40,884 --> 00:14:42,284
No, I didn't lose it.

201
00:14:42,484 --> 00:14:45,284
He gave you the letter, but what am I supposed to do in school?

202
00:14:45,484 --> 00:14:46,884
Listen to yourself.

203
00:14:47,084 --> 00:14:48,084
What?

204
00:14:48,284 --> 00:14:49,684
Have you ever been to a school?

205
00:14:49,884 --> 00:14:50,884
No, unfortunately not.

206
00:14:51,084 --> 00:14:54,484
Why unfortunately? You can be happy that you didn't have to go to school yet.

207
00:14:55,484 --> 00:14:57,084
Did you know what was in the letter?

208
00:14:57,284 --> 00:14:58,684
No, it was sealed.

209
00:14:58,884 --> 00:15:02,084
Grandfather didn't even tell me that I was allowed to go to school.

210
00:15:02,284 --> 00:15:04,684
That's no wonder. That's not normal.

211
00:15:04,884 --> 00:15:06,084
That's mean.

212
00:15:07,084 --> 00:15:07,669
I'm sorry.

213
00:15:07,669 --> 00:15:09,669
Take it back!

214
00:15:10,669 --> 00:15:11,669
Take it back!

215
00:15:11,669 --> 00:15:13,669
Why should he? Everyone says so.

216
00:15:13,669 --> 00:15:15,669
He lives up in the mountains and it's not normal.

217
00:15:15,669 --> 00:15:17,669
That's no wonder.

218
00:15:17,669 --> 00:15:20,669
He lives up there all alone and doesn't want anything to do with anyone.

219
00:15:20,669 --> 00:15:22,669
That's how it is.

220
00:15:22,669 --> 00:15:24,669
You have no idea.

221
00:15:32,597 --> 00:15:35,597
Doesn't she look strange, too?

222
00:15:35,597 --> 00:15:39,597
Heidi, show us the alphabet, will you?

223
00:15:39,597 --> 00:15:41,597
If you tell me what it is, I'd love to.

224
00:15:49,597 --> 00:15:52,597
She doesn't even know what the alphabet is!

225
00:15:53,173 --> 00:15:57,173
Is the alphabet something funny?

226
00:15:57,173 --> 00:15:59,173
The alphabet?

227
00:15:59,173 --> 00:16:01,173
Well, if you've never heard the alphabet,

228
00:16:01,173 --> 00:16:03,173
then we'll teach you two.

229
00:16:03,173 --> 00:16:04,173
Be quiet! Attention!

230
00:16:04,173 --> 00:16:18,173
A, B, C, D, E, F, G, H, I, J, K, L, M, N, O, F, Q, R, S

231
00:16:18,173 --> 00:16:19,173
Stop! Stop! Stop!

232
00:16:19,173 --> 00:16:21,173
You might be a teacher!

233
00:16:21,173 --> 00:16:23,173
You're making mistakes!

234
00:16:27,701 --> 00:16:29,701
Why do you need something like that?

235
00:16:29,701 --> 00:16:31,701
That's not possible!

236
00:16:31,701 --> 00:16:33,701
Tell me!

237
00:16:33,701 --> 00:16:35,701
You don't seem to know anything.

238
00:16:35,701 --> 00:16:37,701
It's about time you came to school.

239
00:16:37,701 --> 00:16:39,701
At least I can milk goats.

240
00:16:39,701 --> 00:16:41,701
And that's better than all of us together.

241
00:16:41,701 --> 00:16:43,701
Everyone in our village can milk goats.

242
00:16:43,701 --> 00:16:45,701
I can whistle, too.

243
00:16:50,283 --> 00:16:55,083
- I can do that too! - I've never seen such a stupid thing like you!

244
00:16:55,283 --> 00:16:56,483
You should be let go!

245
00:16:56,683 --> 00:16:59,083
- Come with me! - You really need the school!

246
00:16:59,283 --> 00:17:01,283
Why are they so close to me?

247
00:17:08,629 --> 00:17:12,629
Why did they laugh at me then? Did I do something to them or did I do something
wrong?

248
00:17:12,629 --> 00:17:17,629
Oh, what? No one has to go to school. They only tell you boring things. Believe
me.

249
00:17:17,629 --> 00:17:18,629
Wait a minute.

250
00:17:20,629 --> 00:17:25,629
So, now everything is fine. Now you can teach me the alphabet. Start with it.

251
00:17:25,629 --> 00:17:27,629
What? I should teach you the alphabet?

252
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:28,629
Yes.

253
00:17:29,629 --> 00:17:30,629
I don't know.

254
00:17:31,629 --> 00:17:34,629
Then don't be so slow. Start.

255
00:17:34,629 --> 00:17:37,629
A, B, C, D.

256
00:17:37,675 --> 00:17:46,475
E, F, G, F, G, F, G, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, G, G.

257
00:17:46,475 --> 00:17:48,475
How does it go on? Don't you know?

258
00:17:48,475 --> 00:17:50,475
G, F, G, M.

259
00:17:50,475 --> 00:17:53,475
Oh, why? No one needs the alphabet.

260
00:17:53,475 --> 00:17:56,475
The goats have never asked us for it, have they?

261
00:17:56,475 --> 00:17:59,475
So I'm not the only one who doesn't know it yet.

262
00:18:00,475 --> 00:18:02,475
Come on, let's go home.

263
00:18:07,675 --> 00:18:10,675
