00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:44,660
This time he will have to read whether he likes it or not.

270
00:18:44,660 --> 00:18:45,660
He doesn't care.

271
00:18:45,660 --> 00:18:46,660
No.

272
00:18:46,660 --> 00:18:48,660
You make me curious. What did he write?

273
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,660
Do you know what's in it?

274
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:54,660
I know. He's supposed to send Heidi to school, but he's going to come up with an
excuse again.

275
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:56,660
My son says she can't even read the alphabet.

276
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:58,346
Is that a possibility?

277
00:18:58,346 --> 00:19:01,946
I'm convinced that she can't even distinguish right from left.

278
00:19:01,946 --> 00:19:04,346
Well, you know what that leads to.

279
00:19:04,346 --> 00:19:08,546
That's not going to end well, because I haven't seen her in the church on Sunday
either.

280
00:19:08,546 --> 00:19:11,046
You can't blame the child for that.

281
00:19:11,082 --> 00:19:13,682
She doesn't go to church herself. How should the little girl know?

282
00:19:13,682 --> 00:19:16,182
You have to be careful that she doesn't even bathe on Saturdays.

283
00:19:16,182 --> 00:19:20,582
My son is bathed every Saturday and scrubbed with soap, whether he wants to or
not.

284
00:19:20,582 --> 00:19:24,582
I don't know, I don't know, I don't know. Maybe she even has lice.

285
00:19:24,582 --> 00:19:27,582
That could be good, but I don't think so.

286
00:19:27,582 --> 00:19:30,582
My son saw her today and said she was a very pretty girl.

287
00:19:30,582 --> 00:19:31,582
He didn't see lice.

288
00:19:31,582 --> 00:19:34,582
The more important it is that she goes to school.

289
00:19:35,482 --> 00:19:38,982
Yes, yes, yes, yes, but the old man doesn't want to listen to us.

290
00:19:38,982 --> 00:19:40,982
He hasn't greeted me a single time.

291
00:19:40,982 --> 00:19:42,982
Recently I even waved to him.

292
00:19:42,982 --> 00:19:44,482
Exactly, that looks like him.

293
00:19:44,482 --> 00:19:46,482
He looks through you as if you were air.

294
00:20:02,482 --> 00:20:04,482
Grandfather, I'm back!

295
00:20:04,482 --> 00:20:06,482
Finally!

296
00:20:06,482 --> 00:20:09,482
I was down in the village and visited Schnucki.

297
00:20:11,220 --> 00:20:15,520
- There I am! - You're late, I just put on my coat and wanted to look for you.

298
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:17,120
I was at Schnucki's.

299
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:19,520
She's fine and she shouldn't be sold anymore.

300
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:21,120
Oh, I'm glad to hear that.

301
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:23,720
Yes, and imagine, she's still giving milk.

302
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:28,948
That's good for me.

303
00:20:28,948 --> 00:20:31,748
My hands are freezing cold. Show me the letter.

304
00:20:31,748 --> 00:20:36,748
Down in the village, they say, the teacher has written that I can also come to
school now.

305
00:20:37,748 --> 00:20:39,948
So they told you about it?

306
00:20:39,948 --> 00:20:43,948
Was that wrong? Why are you so angry all of a sudden?

307
00:20:46,348 --> 00:20:48,948
Why didn't you tell me anything about school?

308
00:20:51,748 --> 00:20:53,948
Because I don't think it's right.

309
00:20:55,948 --> 00:20:57,948
Have you never been to school?

310
00:20:58,281 --> 00:21:02,281
Yes, that's true, but this school is down in the village, and that's something
else.

311
00:21:02,281 --> 00:21:05,781
But there's no other one, and I have to go to school.

312
00:21:05,781 --> 00:21:06,781
You don't.

313
00:21:07,781 --> 00:21:10,281
That's enough, I don't want to hear any more of that.

314
00:21:13,281 --> 00:21:15,281
Why?

315
00:21:22,099 --> 00:21:24,099
Why?

316
00:21:24,099 --> 00:21:27,099
It's a waste of time to go to school.

317
00:21:28,099 --> 00:21:32,099
They teach the children how to write and read, but they also spoil them.

318
00:21:32,099 --> 00:21:38,099
They forget to teach the children that there is something more important for
people than letters and numbers.

319
00:21:38,099 --> 00:21:42,099
They look at our world in books and no longer know how beautiful it really is.

320
00:21:42,099 --> 00:21:45,099
But you still know.

321
00:21:46,099 --> 00:21:48,099
I don't know.

322
00:21:49,811 --> 00:21:54,811
Then you bring me the writing and reading. It's enough for both of us when you
were in school.

323
00:21:56,811 --> 00:21:59,811
I'll make us something to eat. You've been in the fresh air all day.

324
00:22:00,811 --> 00:22:01,811
Good, I'm hungry.

325
00:22:07,091 --> 00:22:14,091
When Heidi then sat at the dinner table with her grandfather, she had long
forgotten the plan to go to school

326
00:22:14,091 --> 00:22:21,091
She told in detail about what she had experienced, about Snooki, about the milk
that Snooki gave and about the snowball battle of course

327
00:22:21,091 --> 00:22:29,091
She didn't read anything in her report, not even that she was laughed at by the
village boys and that Peter couldn't read the alphabet

328
00:22:29,091 --> 00:22:36,091
She told about the big sled and the cow bell and claimed that they would have
been faster than the wind

329
00:22:37,091 --> 00:22:43,091
The End

330
00:22:43,795 --> 00:22:51,795
When the snow melted and it became spring, Heidi and Joseph ran across the
meadows every day and looked for new adventures.

331
00:22:51,795 --> 00:22:56,795
And on one of these trains they both experienced a surprise.

332
00:22:58,795 --> 00:23:00,795
Watch out, he's flying far!

333
00:23:03,795 --> 00:23:07,795
A stranger man came up to them, whom Heidi had never seen before.

334
00:23:07,795 --> 00:23:09,795
What did he want up here?

335
00:23:10,265 --> 00:23:18,765
He was friendly to her and spoke for a long time with the grandfather. Heidi was
not allowed to be there when the two were having a conversation, but the
grandfather was very serious.

336
00:23:18,765 --> 00:23:22,265
But we want to tell you about this in our next story.

337
00:23:23,007 --> 00:23:52,007
Heidi, Heidi, your world is the mountains, Heidi, Heidi, because up here you are
at home, Heidi, Heidi, come home, find your happiness, come back home.

338
00:23:53,007 --> 00:23:54,360
Thank you for watching.

